    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Service Manual - High-pressure Oil Pump - Installation - High-pressure Oil Pump Cover</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26511.4.3" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>High-pressure Oil Pump Cover</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new gasket in the recess in the high-pressure oil pump (if not already done).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001222" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11042.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Lubricating the high-pressure oil pump O-ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate high-pressure oil pump O-ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001223" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figJ11/J11043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) to crankcase and rear cover joining surfaces</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply Liquid Gasket (RTV) to locations where rear cover, high-pressure pump cover and
                crankcase join. See
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_259.xml" xrefid="E30012C">Special Service Tools</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001224" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11036.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the high-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, the high-pressure oil pump cover must be firmly seated onto the
                    high-pressure oil pump O-ring to prevent cracking the cover plate.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="e3001225" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Seating the high-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply firm even downward pressure to seat the high-pressure oil pump cover over the
                high-pressure pump O-ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="e3001226" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figj11/J11045.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Torque the high-pressure oil pump cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install eight mounting bolts (M6 x 25) and tighten to the
                <hotlnk document="eges3001_258.xml" xrefid="E30012B" appearance="hottext">Special Torque</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to Engine Electrical Components for IPR valve installation procedure.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall all safety guards, shields, and covers after servicing the engine. Make sure all
                tools, covers, loose parts and service equipment are removed from engine area after all work is done.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
